      <p><strong>Result:</strong> Compound fine RM500-RM2,000. Lorry impounded. Business shut down until permit obtained.</p>

      <p>APAD (Agensi Kualiti dan Keselamatan Jalan Raya) permits are mandatory for all commercial lorries in Malaysia. Operating without one isn't just illegal—it's business suicide.</p>

      <h2>What is APAD Permit?</h2>

      <h3>Overview</h3>

      <p>APAD permit (formerly JPJ permit) is:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Official License:</strong> Required for all goods vehicles</li>
        <li><strong>Issued By:</strong> Road Transport Department (JPJ) under APAD authority</li>
        <li><strong>Valid For:</strong> 1-2 years depending on permit type</li>
        <li><strong>Required For:</strong> Any lorry used for commercial transport</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Permit Types</h3>

      <p><strong>Goods Vehicle License (GVL):</strong>
      <br>• For lorries transporting goods
      <br>• Required for all commercial lorries
      <br>• Valid: 1-2 years</p>

      <p><strong>Public Service Vehicle License (PSV):</strong>
      <br>• For lorries providing passenger transport
      <br>• Specialized requirements
      <br>• Valid: 1 year</p>

      <p><strong>International Permit:</strong>
      <br>• For cross-border operations (Thailand, Singapore)
      <br>• Additional documentation
      <br>• Valid: 6 months - 1 year</p>

      <h2>APAD Permit Requirements</h2>

      <h3>Documentation Needed</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Business Registration:</strong> SSM certificate (for companies)</li>
        <li><strong>Lorry Registration:</strong> JPJ registration card</li>
        <li><strong>Insurance Coverage:</strong> Comprehensive insurance proof</li>
        <li><strong>PUSPAKOM Inspection:</strong> Valid inspection report</li>
        <li><strong>Driver License:</strong> Valid GDL (Goods Driving License)</li>
        <li><strong>Ownership Proof:</strong> Financing agreement or sale certificate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Vehicle Requirements</h3>

      <p>Lorry must meet:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Age Limit:</strong> Under 10 years old (some permits allow up to 15 years)</li>
        <li><strong>Condition:</strong> Roadworthy (PUSPAKOM certified)</li>
        <li><strong>Equipment:</strong> Reflective tape, proper lighting, load securing equipment</li>
        <li><strong>Weight Limits:</strong> Within registered load capacity</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>APAD Permit Costs</h2>

      <h3>Application Fees</h3>

      <p><strong>New Permit Application:</strong>
      <br>• Processing fee: RM50-RM100
      <br>• Permit fee: RM200-RM600 (depending on lorry type)
      <br>• Card issuance: RM20-RM50</p>

      <p><strong>Permit Renewal:</strong>
      <br>• Renewal fee: RM200-RM600
      <br>• Late penalty: Up to RM100</p>

      <h3>Permit Costs by Lorry Type</h3>

